An Ado Ekiti Chief Magistrate’s Court has ordered that a 29-year-old man, Ayokunle Henry be remanded in prison over alleged rape. The accused committed the offence on 28 December, 2019 in Ilawe-Ekiti, headquarters of Ekiti Southwest local government area of Ekiti state. The offence contravened section 2(2) of Ekiti State Gender Based Violence (Prohibition) Amended Law, 2019. The police prosecutor, Inspector Caleb Leranmo, told the court that the accused hanged-out with the victim, a 17-year-old girl before he allegedly took her to the bush and raped her. Leranmo urged the court to remand the defendant in prison pending legal advice from office of Director of Public Prosecution (DPP). The accused’s plea was not taken. The Chief Magistrate, Mr. Abdulhamid Lawal, ordered the remand of the accused in prison, pending the issuance of legal advice and adjourned the case till February 3rd for mention.